            "text": "According to Carter, he complied with the state's laws to obtain the van, but the Godin family claims that he had illegally removed the vehicle from their property. According to the Godin's, the van holds sentimental value, and they had planned on restoring Wild Cherry themselves. Despite not being registered since the early '90s, Laura Godin said, \"Nobody has the right to go onto anybody's property and do this.\" She also said that the title was actually inside the van at the time, but after Carter ",
